:parcel <<'/---'
Document all globals, functions, and aliases declared by @{*-global}.
/---

# ....................{ GLOBALS                            }....................
:string_global ZESHY_VAR_NAME_GLOB <<'/---'
Glob matching syntactically valid `zsh` variable names.
/---

:string_global\
    ZESHY_DECLARATION_GLOBAL_NAMES_AND_VALUE_GLOB <<'/---'
Glob matching syntactically valid `=`-delimited global declarations initializing
one or more global names to one value. On a successful match, such glob captures
the following groups from such declarations:

* `${match[1]}`, providing all `=`-suffixed global names in such declaration.
* `${match[2]}`, providing the value such globals should be initialized to.
/---

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
